{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/2014/11/07/interactive-light-sculptures/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://blog.aboutme.be"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"2b184c4e-b6cc-57e0-9766-e39a5e4f0694","excerpt":"A couple of weeks back, my Happy-Banana partner in crime Koen and I were approached by artist Tom Dekyvere for an interactive sculpture project. He wanted to…","html":"<p>A couple of weeks back, my Happy-Banana partner in crime Koen and I were approached by artist <a href=\"http://tomandliendekyvere.com/\">Tom Dekyvere</a> for an interactive sculpture project.</p>\n<p>He wanted to put interactive artworks at the Catch festival in Utrecht and was looking for a partner to help build the electronics. The sculptures needed to respond with light and sound on the people around. Challenge accepted!</p>\n<p>We started experimenting with different libraries and electronics, and quickly settled on the <a href=\"https://sensorium.github.io/Mozzi/\">Mozzi library</a> for Arduino Sound synthesis on the software side, together with a maxbotix ultrasonic distance sensor, mosfet and some 12V ledstrips. Our first experiments were promising:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/432268662\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen=\"\" style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>\n<p>The next step was replicating this 6 times, which proved to take more time than we thought. We finished soldering the final board just when Tom was here to pick up our hardware!</p>\n<p>Here’s a clip where you can see Tom’s sculptures lighting up and reacting to the audience:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 42.5%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/432275416\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen=\"\" style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>","fields":{"slug":"/2014/11/07/interactive-light-sculptures/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Interactive Light Sculptures","date":"07 Nov, 2014","description":false,"tags":["arduino","sound","sculptures","interactive"],"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/preview.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/3c249/preview.jpg","srcSet":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/3c249/preview.jpg 690w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/956b7/preview.avif 690w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/37026/preview.webp 690w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":1.3333333333333333}}}}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018/10/10/quick-hack-timing-air-pump-with-arduino/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Quick Hack, Timing an Air Pump with Arduino","tags":["arduino","installation"],"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/77b06fcf3f099b0cb43897e9e3e66f0a/preview.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/77b06fcf3f099b0cb43897e9e3e66f0a/3c249/preview.jpg","srcSet":"/static/77b06fcf3f099b0cb43897e9e3e66f0a/3c249/preview.jpg 690w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/77b06fcf3f099b0cb43897e9e3e66f0a/956b7/preview.avif 690w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/77b06fcf3f099b0cb43897e9e3e66f0a/37026/preview.webp 690w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"100vw"}]},"width":1,"height":1.3333333333333333}}}}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug"